The Lagos State Scout Commissioner, Alhaji Olohuntoyin Adebeshin, has said that for the country’s economy to be viable again, the youths must be empowered. Speaking during the Lagos State Scout Council’s end of year ceremony and empowerment initiative, Adeboshin noted that the initiative was part of his administration’s effort to support the most vulnerable in the council through job creation and provision of a sustainable support mechanism. He urged the young scouts to harness the opportunities in their areas of skills and knowledge to advance their livelihoods and attain sustainable socioeconomic wellbeing, calling for more support from government and private individuals to the project. Copyright PUNCH All rights reserved. This material, and other digital content on this website, may not be reproduced, published, broadcast, rewritten or redistributed in whole or in part without prior express written permission from PUNCH. Contact: theeditor@punchng.com